node.text:
An exclusive short film for #SSENSE and @burberry directed by @torso.solutions. Starring Lourdes Leon, @thereal_chopchop, and @trapselyna, our protagonists imprint memories upon the city, featuring vignettes from @brontezpurnell, @julianahuxtable and Natasha Stagg.

Screening at Burberry SoHo from June 17-26 alongside Burberry’s Mythical Alphabet, an exclusive capsule collection designed in collaboration with @petersavilleartwork and @jo_can_draw. Link in bio for the digital rendition of our store takeover: Imaginary Cities. #BurberryxSSENSE #BurberrysMythicalAlphabet

node.text: Living in the absence of our everyday, #SSENSE and @Burberry extend the incomplete sensorial works of Italo Calvino's "Under the Jaguar Sun". Shop the SS21 collection now.

node.text: How did @JerryLorenzo start his career in fashion? What is his life motto? How does he view @FearOfGod vs. @Essentials? To celebrate “SEVEN DAYS TO FOREVER” with #FearOfGod, an immersive digital experience by #SSENSE, we asked the designer and founder a few questions. Keep your eyes peeled for daily updates on our week of releases, starting tomorrow. Link in bio for more.

node.title: SSENSE and Reebok by Pyer Moss: “What’s Your Story?”

node.text:
In honor of the British designer’s unfaltering influence—and his exclusive FW20 spaghetti print for SSENSE—we’ve asked artists @david_jien, @0h_heck, @bensandersstudio, @janiekorn, and @nikkogary to reimagine @paulsmith's most meaningful collector’s items from the past five decades. 

Reflections and reminiscences are laced throughout the designer’s growing collection of paraphernalia: artworks, objects, and observations from the people and places that have inspired his anti-minimalist, awe-inspiring vision. Discover @paulsmithdesign’s 50th anniversary story, available now on #SSENSE

node.title: 50 Years, Five Artists, and Paul Smith’s Unwavering Curiosity

node.text: Brrr! It's cold in here, I said there must be some Clovers In the atmosphere… Two decades later, we still know all the words to “Bring It On” and every scene with Torrance, Iris, the Rancho Carne Toros, and the East Compton Clovers. To celebrate the film’s 20th anniversary, @saraheramos creates an homage to everyone’s favorite cheerleading film with @lauraharrier, @vanessalchester, and @meaganholder 🤸 Comment below with your favorite part from the movie.

node.text:
“It’s not about genre. It’s about your vibe and your willingness to contribute to the conversation in a way that’s meaningful and isn’t about building your social capital, or about monetary success. Sometimes it’s about similar moral values, sometimes it’s just about sharing a friend group. It’s not about conforming to a certain style, it’s about doing what you feel.” @en_hakim speaks to @ross_scarano about disregarding genre and what collaboration has been like under quarantine. You’re also listening to (*sound on*) an unreleased demo of his single “QADIR”, performed with Roy Nathanson in his living room. 

Check our story for more on what Nick is listening to lately (and always) 🎶 Link in bio for the interview.
